@node bugs "Known problems and bugs"
@{b}Known problems and problems@{ub}@{line}

Well I don't know about bugs but there are some problems (at least one): if,
else and endif don't work in BetterStartup. I know it works well in AmigaDOS
scripts but I don't know how to make BetterStartup to use it and I'm too lazy to
implement my own way of if/else/endif. So if you really need them, use external
script for that or modify BetterStartup.script the way it won't need them
anymore. Or even better, send me how to make AmigaDOS if/else/endif work in my
program. Thanx.@{line}

You might have also some other problems (in which cases BetterStartup can even
crash Amiga completely). Please, if you have, don't write me only that your
Amiga crashes with BetterStartup, please, @{b}send@{ub} me your
BetterStartup.script. Although I cannot promise that I will recover it I will do
my best. So again, send me your BetterStartup.script, otherwise I'm nearly not
able to do anything about it. Thanx.
@endnode
@node history "History of BetterStartup"
@{b}History@{ub}@{line}

    1.4 (37.215, 14th November 1996)@{line}
        - minor bug fixed in OnePromote - could promote to incorrect mode@{line}
          (e.g. prefs for new MagicMenu)@{line}
@{line}
    1.3 (37.214, 2nd February 1996)@{line}
	- bug fixed - caused to execute @GUI-@ENDGUI section even when@{line}
	   gui was not to be opened@{line}
	- screen is forced to get into front - corrects problems of@{line}
	   PicBoot program with PATCH switch on@{line}
	- some easy optimalization of opening window@{line}
	- #CHOICES new internal command added@{line}
@{line}
    1.2 (37.210, 28th January 1996)@{line}
	- third public release@{line}
	- minor bug in OnePromote fixed (e.g. problems with SwazBlanker)@{line}
	- one more minor bug in OnePromote fixed (the patch to@{line}
	   OpenScreen() function)@{line}
@{line}
    1.1 (37.208, 17th December 1995)@{line}
	- second public release@{line}
	- major bug removed: it crashed when there were no options defined@{line}
	   (so it crashed if you followed the installation process)@{line}
	- new feature: &ELSE posibility for &CHECKBOX@{line}
	- one minor bug removed@{line}
@{line}
    1.0 (37.204, 5th April 1995)@{line}
	- first public release@{line}
@endnode
@node future "Future of BetterStartup"
@{b}Future@{ub}@{line}

Although I have some other plans in near future, it may happen I will finaly
start work on the new version of BetterStartup. I have many many ideas in
my head, some of them are here for you to taste. Anyway, I'm going to finish
my Master's soon (May 97) so I'll be very busy with studies. I still hope
I'll make these ideas into a program:

- BetterStartup changed from boot menu program with add-ons into independent
  startup program
- Modular design - while installing you'll select what you want to use and
  what not. The executable will then be just that long
- Boot menu as one of modules
- Modules based on a kind of module interface, docs with BetterStartup how to
  write your own module with examples
- Modules means no more MCP or MagicCX in memory with half of stuff unused
  (just someone has to rewrite all the patches from these programs into
  modules :-(
- Script system completely reworked to face the change to modules
- And hopefuly the GUI editor finaly as well

If you have new ideas, just write me, I'll see, maybe I'll like them.
@endnode
